  faqs: [
    {
      question: 'How do you assess the health of our existing database without disrupting production?',
      answer: 'We use read-only diagnostic tooling exclusively during the assessment phase. For PostgreSQL, this includes pg_stat_statements, pg_stat_user_tables, pg_stat_user_indexes and EXPLAIN ANALYZE on captured slow queries. For other engines, we use equivalent native tooling. We never run modifications or schema changes in production without explicit, written sign-off, and all changes are preceded by tested rollback procedures. The assessment phase is entirely non-destructive.',
    },
